comments: Jones (NOP) moves laterally into Batum's (LAC) path at the start of his drive and marginal contact occurs.
McCollum (NOP) jumps towards Powell (LAC) and makes marginal contact to his arm after the release of his jump shot attempt.
McCollum (NOP) grasps Powell's (LAC) jersey as he deflects the ball away.
Powell (LAC) reaches around McCollum (NOP) and dislodges the ball from him before incidental contact occurs.
Powell (LAC) is the last person to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds. The possession is correctly awarded to NOP.
Morris Sr. (LAC) fails to fully clear the lane and is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Morris Sr. (LAC) places his forearm against Murphy III's (NOP) body after his gather and marginal contact occurs.
Jackson (LAC) places his arm against Murphy III's (NOP) body underneath the rim and marginal contact occurs as they pursue the loose ball.
Jones (NOP) maintains legal guarding position moving along Morris Sr.'s (LAC) path and marginal contact occurs defending his drive to the basket.
Jones (NOP) makes marginal contact to Covington's (LAC) lower body contesting his shot attempt at the basket.
Ingram (NOP) comes to a stop after the pick and slightly extends his arm against Batum's (LAC) body as he releases away from the contact.

Replay review of the foul called on Batum (LAC) pursuant to a coach?s challenge was deemed unsuccessful. Batum (LAC) extends his hand against Jones' (NOP) body and the contact dislodge him from his obtain position.
Powell (LAC) makes contact with the ball during McCollum's (NOP) drive and cleanly dislodges the ball before incidental contact occurs.
Batum (LAC) makes marginal contact with Murphy III's (NOP) hand after the release of his jump shot attempt.
Nance Jr. (NOP) delivers contact to Jackson's (LAC) body after his gather and the contact affects his driving shot attempt.
Jackson (LAC) trialing Ingram (NOP) as he gathers the inbound pass and makes marginal contact to his lower body as they separate.
Murphy III (NOP) establishes himself in a screening position in Covington's (LAC) path and makes marginal contact as they disengage.
Batum (LAC) places a collasping forearm to Ingram's (NOP) side and makes marginal contact as he releases his pass attempt.
Covington (LAC) is the last person to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds. The possession is correctly awarded to NOP.
Covington (LAC) commits a take foul on Nance Jr. (NOP).
Nance Jr. (NOP) hedges the hand-off and initiates contact to Powell's (LAC) body that affects his SQBR.
Covington (LAC) makes contact with the ball after Ingram (NOP) gathers the pass and makes marginal contact to his arm as he slides his hand off the ball.
Morris Sr. (LAC) makes marginal contact to Valanciunas' (NOP) backside contesting his shot attempt at the basket.

Jones (NOP) arm is slightly extended contesting Jackson's (LAC) jump shot attempt and makes marginal contact to his face after the release of his jump shot attempt.  Contact to an opponent?s head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
McCollum (NOP) places a resting hand to Morris Sr.'s (LAC) side during his upward shooting motion and removes it without apply force defending his jump shot attempt.
